{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857051412,"sessionID":"ses_286ac20beffe44cAD1ncYYIIxq","part":{"id":"prt_d7954225d001Ey4ws1xa1a7OT9","messageID":"msg_d795411cb00177XtyxAXXeJaqC","sessionID":"ses_286ac20beffe44cAD1ncYYIIxq","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_467ef0d6161b4a29b2767c0e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Specification — AR-012: Session Store Interface\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **Module:** `pkg/store`  \n6: **Language:** Go  \n7: **Size:** S  \n8: **Type:** New feature — Session persistence layer for sandbox orchestration\n9: \n10: ---\n11: \n12: ## Requirements & Scenarios\n13: \n14: ### REQ-001: Store Interface Contract\n15: \n16: **Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n17: \n18: #### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n19: - **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n20: - **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called\n21: - **THEN** the implementation issues PING and requires string response `PONG`\n22: \n23: #### Scenario: Store interface implemented by Redis\n24: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=redis`\n25: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n26: - **THEN** the returned `Store` is `*redisStore` implementing all 9 methods\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Store interface implemented by Valkey\n29: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n30: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n31: - **THEN** the returned `Store` is `*valkeyStore` implementing all 9 methods\n32: \n33: ---\n34: \n35: ### REQ-002: Not Found Semantics\n36: \n37: **Requirement:** The system SHALL return package error `ErrNotFound` (message `store: not found`) when a session key is absent on read or when last-activity update targets a missing session.\n38: \n39: #### Scenario: Get missing session returns ErrNotFound\n40: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n41: - **WHEN** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` runs\n42: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound` (Redis: `redis.Nil`; Valkey: `IsValkeyNil`)\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Update last-activity on missing session\n45: - **GIVEN** no key `session:{id}` in backend\n46: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, id, time.Now())` is called\n47: - **THEN** error is `ErrNotFound`\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ### REQ-003: Session Key Naming\n52: \n53: **Requirement:** The system SHALL use string prefix `session:` concatenated with the session id as the primary key for JSON document storage.\n54: \n55: #### Scenario: Key construction\n56: - **GIVEN** session id `abc-123`\n57: - **WHEN** the store writes sandbox data\n58: - **THEN** the string key is `session:abc-123`\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ### REQ-004: Expiry Index (Sorted Set)\n63: \n64: **Requirement:** The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:expiry` with member = session id and score = `ExpiresAt` Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL add the member with the sandbox expiry score. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL remove the member.\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n67: - **GIVEN** a new sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Unix(1000, 0)`\n68: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` succeeds\n69: - **THEN** `session:expiry` contains member `sandbox.SessionID` with score `1000`\n70: \n71: #### Scenario: List expired uses ZRANGEBYSCORE\n72: - **GIVEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` with limit > 0\n73: - **WHEN** the implementation queries the index\n74: - **THEN** it selects members with scores from `-inf` through `before.Unix()`, limited to `limit` entries\n75: \n76: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from expiry index\n77: - **GIVEN** session `abc` exists in `session:expiry` ZSET\n78: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` succeeds\n79: - **THEN** `session:expiry` no longer contains member `abc`\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ### REQ-005: Last-Activity Index (Sorted Set)\n84: \n85: **Requirement:** The system SHALL maintain sorted set key `session:last_activity` with member = session id and score = last activity Unix seconds. `StoreSandbox` SHALL ZADD with score `time.Now().Unix()` on initial store. `UpdateSessionLastActivity` SHALL ZADD with the provided timestamp. `DeleteSandboxBySessionID` SHALL ZREM the member.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: StoreSandbox initializes last-activity\n88: - **GIVEN** a new sandbox being stored at time `T`\n89: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` succeeds\n90: - **THEN** `session:last_activity` contains member `sandbox.SessionID` with score `T.Unix()`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: List inactive uses activity index\n93: - **GIVEN** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)`\n94: - **WHEN** executed\n95: - **THEN** members with last-activity score ≤ `before.Unix()` are returned up to `limit`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: UpdateSessionLastActivity bumps timestamp\n98: - **GIVEN** session `abc` with last-activity score `1000`\n99: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Unix(2000, 0))` succeeds\n100: - **THEN** `session:last_activity` member `abc` has score `2000`\n101: \n102: #### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from activity index\n103: - **GIVEN** session `abc` exists in `session:last_activity` ZSET\n104: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\")` succeeds\n105: - **THEN** `session:last_activity` no longer contains member `abc`\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: ### REQ-006: StoreSandbox Atomicity and Validation\n110: \n111: **Requirement:** The system SHALL reject nil sandbox or zero `ExpiresAt`. The system SHALL execute SETNX on session key, ZADD expiry, and ZADD last_activity in one pipeline/multi block. The system SHALL fail if any command in the batch errors.\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n114: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, nil)`\n115: - **WHEN** called\n116: - **THEN** error indicates sandbox is nil (no backend operation)\n117: \n118: #### Scenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n119: - **GIVEN** sandbox with `ExpiresAt = time.Time{}` (zero value)\n120: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called\n121: - **THEN** error indicates ExpiresAt is invalid (no backend operation)\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: Duplicate store fails (SETNX)\n124: - **GIVEN** session `abc` already exists in backend\n125: - **WHEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` with same `SessionID` is called\n126: - **THEN** operation fails (SETNX returns 0)\n127: \n128: #### Scenario: Pipeline atomicity\n129: - **GIVEN** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` with valid data\n130: - **WHEN** pipeline executes SETNX, ZADD expiry, ZADD last_activity\n131: - **THEN** all three succeed or all fail; no partial writes\n132: \n133: ---\n134: \n135: ### REQ-007: UpdateSandbox Semantics\n136: \n137: **Requirement:** The system SHALL update only the session JSON value using SET with XX (key must exist). The system SHALL NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries in this operation.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Update existing session\n140: - **GIVEN** session `abc` exists with JSON value V1\n141: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` with updated data succeeds\n142: - **THEN** JSON value is V2; `session:expiry` and `session:last_activity` unchanged\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Missing key on update\n145: - **GIVEN** session key `session:abc` does not exist\n146: - **WHEN** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` runs\n147: - **THEN** Redis: `SETXX` returns false → error; Valkey: response not `\"OK\"` → error\n148: \n149: ---\n150: \n151: ### REQ-008: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Cleanup\n152: \n153: **Requirement:** The system SHALL delete session key and remove session id from both sorted sets in one pipeline/multi.\n154: \n155: #### Scenario: Full removal\n156: - **GIVEN** an existing session in main key + both ZSETs\n157: - **WHEN** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, id)` succeeds\n158: - **THEN** GET `session:{id}` returns not found AND both ZSETs no longer contain the member\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ### REQ-009: List Loaders Tolerate Missing Keys\n163: \n164: **Requirement:** When listing by ZSET returns session ids, the system SHALL load JSON per id; SHALL skip entries where the string key is missing without failing the whole batch.\n165: \n166: #### Scenario: Orphan ZSET member skipped\n167: - **GIVEN** a session id in `session:expiry` ZSET without a string value\n168: - **WHEN** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs(ctx, ids)` runs\n169: - **THEN** that id is omitted from the returned slice (no error)\n170: \n171: #### Scenario: Partial MGET success\n172: - **GIVEN** 5 session ids in ZSET; 3 have string values, 2 are orphaned\n173: - **WHEN** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 10)` runs\n174: - **THEN** returns slice of 3 sandboxes (orphans skipped silently)\n175: \n176: ---\n177: \n178: ### REQ-010: UpdateSessionLastActivity Preconditions\n179: \n180: **Requirement:** The system SHALL reject empty session id. If `at` is zero time, the system SHALL use `time.Now()`. The system SHALL verify the session key exists before ZADD; if absent, SHALL return `ErrNotFound`.\n181: \n182: #### Scenario: Empty session id rejected\n183: - **GIVEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", time.Now())`\n184: - **WHEN** called\n185: - **THEN** error indicates session id is empty\n186: \n187: #### Scenario: Zero time uses Now\n188: - **GIVEN** session `abc` exists; `at = time.Time{}`\n189: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Time{})` is called\n190: - **THEN** ZADD uses `time.Now().Unix()` as score\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Activity bump for unknown session\n193: - **GIVEN** no `session:{id}` key\n194: - **WHEN** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, id, time.Now())` is called\n195: - **THEN** return `ErrNotFound` (no ZADD performed)\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ### REQ-011: Provider Selection via STORE_TYPE\n200: \n201: **Requirement:** The system SHALL read `STORE_TYPE` case-insensitively; if unset, SHALL default to `redis`. Supported values SHALL be `redis` and `valkey`; any other value SHALL fail initialization.\n202: \n203: #### Scenario: Default redis\n204: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE` is not set\n205: - **WHEN** `Storage()` first initializes\n206: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n207: \n208: #### Scenario: Case-insensitive store type\n209: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=REDIS` or `STORE_TYPE=Redis`\n210: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n211: - **THEN** Redis implementation is constructed\n212: \n213: #### Scenario: Valkey selected\n214: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=valkey`\n215: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n216: - **THEN** Valkey implementation is constructed\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Invalid store type fails\n219: - **GIVEN** `STORE_TYPE=memcached`\n220: - **WHEN** `Storage()` initializes\n221: - **THEN** initialization fails with error indicating unsupported store type\n222: \n223: ---\n224: \n225: ### REQ-012: Redis Environment and Password Policy\n226: \n227: **Requirement:** The system SHALL require `REDIS_ADDR`. The system SHALL require non-empty `REDIS_PASSWORD` unless `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` is set case-insensitively to `false`.\n228: \n229: #### Scenario: Password required by default\n230: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` unset\n231: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n232: - **THEN** initialization fails with error stating password required\n233: \n234: #### Scenario: Password disabled explicitly\n235: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` set, `REDIS_PASSWORD` empty, `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`\n236: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n237: - **THEN** connection proceeds with empty password\n238: \n239: #### Scenario: Password provided\n240: - **GIVEN** `REDIS_ADDR` and `REDIS_PASSWORD` both set\n241: - **WHEN** Redis store initializes\n242: - **THEN** connection uses provided password\n243: \n244: ---\n245: \n246: ### REQ-013: Valkey Environment and Options\n247: \n248: **Requirement:** The system SHALL require `VALKEY_ADDR` (comma-separated addresses split for `InitAddress`). The system SHALL require non-empty `VALKEY_PASSWORD` unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false`. The system SHALL set `DisableCache` true when `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` parses as true; SHALL set `ForceSingleClient` true when `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` parses as true.\n249: \n250: #### Scenario: Comma-separated addresses\n251: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_ADDR=node1:6379,node2:6379,node3:6379`\n252: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n253: - **THEN** `InitAddress` contains three addresses\n254: \n255: #### Scenario: Optional client flags — DisableCache\n256: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=true`\n257: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n258: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is true on `ClientOption`\n259: \n260: #### Scenario: Optional client flags — ForceSingle\n261: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=true`\n262: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n263: - **THEN** `ForceSingleClient` is true on `ClientOption`\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Invalid boolean falls back to false\n266: - **GIVEN** `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=maybe`\n267: - **WHEN** Valkey client options are built\n268: - **THEN** `DisableCache` is false (ParseBool fails)\n269: \n270: ---\n271: \n272: ### REQ-014: Singleton Access\n273: \n274: **Requirement:** The system SHALL expose `func Storage() Store` using `sync.Once`; failed init SHALL log fatal via klog.\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Single initialization\n277: - **GIVEN** multiple goroutines call `Storage()` concurrently\n278: - **WHEN** they run at the same time\n279: - **THEN** `initStore` executes exactly once\n280: \n281: #### Scenario: Fatal on init failure\n282: - **GIVEN** invalid configuration (e.g., missing `REDIS_ADDR`)\n283: - **WHEN** `Storage()` is called\n284: - **THEN** klog.Fatalf is invoked with error message\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ## Data Types\n289: \n290: ### SandboxInfo (from `pkg/common/types`)\n291: \n292: ```go\n293: type SandboxInfo struct {\n294:     Kind             string              `json:\"kind\"`\n295:     SandboxID        string              `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n296:     SandboxNamespace string              `json:\"sandboxNamespace\"`\n297:     Name             string              `json:\"name\"`\n298:     EntryPoints      []SandboxEntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n299:     SessionID        string              `json:\"sessionId\"`\n300:     CreatedAt        time.Time           `json:\"createdAt\"`\n301:     ExpiresAt        time.Time           `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n302:     Status           string              `json:\"status\"`\n303: }\n304: \n305: type SandboxEntryPoint struct {\n306:     Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n307:     Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n308:     Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n309: }\n310: ```\n311: \n312: ---\n313: \n314: ## Key Patterns\n315: \n316: | Component | Pattern |\n317: |-----------|---------|\n318: | Session document | `session:{sessionID}` |\n319: | Expiry index | `session:expiry` (ZSET: member=sessionID, score=ExpiresAt.Unix()) |\n320: | Last-activity index | `session:last_activity` (ZSET: member=sessionID, score=LastActivity.Unix()) |\n321: \n322: ---\n323: \n324: ## Error Definitions\n325: \n326: ```go\n327: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n328: ```\n329: \n330: ---\n331: \n332: ## Environment Variables\n333: \n334: | Variable | Required | Default | Notes |\n335: |----------|----------|---------|-------|\n336: | `STORE_TYPE` | No | `redis` | Case-insensitive; `redis` or `valkey` |\n337: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Yes (if redis) | — | Redis server address |\n338: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Yes unless disabled | — | Empty allowed if `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n339: | `REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive; set to `false` to allow empty password |\n340: | `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes (if valkey) | — | Comma-separated addresses |\n341: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless disabled | — | Empty allowed if `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` |\n342: | `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | `true` | Case-insensitive |\n343: | `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | `false` | ParseBool; enables `DisableCache` if true |\n344: | `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | `false` | ParseBool; enables `ForceSingleClient` if true |\n345: \n346: ---\n347: \n348: ## Implementation Notes\n349: \n350: ### Redis Client\n351: - Library: `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9`\n352: - Type: `*redisv9.Client`\n353: - Pipeline: Used for `StoreSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`\n354: \n355: ### Valkey Client\n356: - Library: `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go`\n357: - Type: `valkey.Client`\n358: - MGET: Used in `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` (requires same slot deployment consideration)\n359: \n360: ### Zero-Limit Handling\n361: - `ListExpiredSandboxes` / `ListInactiveSandboxes` with `limit <= 0` returns `nil, nil`\n362: \n363: ---\n364: \n365: ## Acceptance Checklist\n366: \n367: - [ ] `pkg/store/store.go` — Store interface with 9 methods + `ErrNotFound`\n368: - [ ] `pkg/store/singleton.go` — `Storage()`, `initStore()`, provider constants\n369: - [ ] `pkg/store/store_redis.go` — Redis implementation with pipeline operations\n370: - [ ] `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` — Valkey implementation with DoMulti operations\n371: - [ ] `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go` — `SandboxInfo`, `SandboxEntryPoint` types\n372: - [ ] Unit tests for all 14 requirements with GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios\n373: - [ ] Integration tests with real Redis and Valkey instances\n\n(End of file - total 373 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Specification — AR-012: Session Store Interface\n\n## Overview\n\n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** New feature — Session persistence layer for sandbox orchestration\n\n---\n\n## Requirements & Scenarios\n\n### REQ-001: Store Interface Contract\n\n**Requirement:** The system SHALL provide a `Store` interface implemented by Redis and Valkey providers with methods: `Ping`, `GetSandboxBySessionID`, `StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`, `DeleteSandboxBySessionID`, `ListExpiredSandboxes`, `ListInactiveSandboxes`, `UpdateSessionLastActivity`, and `Close`.\n\n#### Scenario: Ping verifies connectivity\n- **GIVEN** a healthy Redis/Valkey server\n- **WHEN** `Ping(ctx)` is called","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857051399,"end":1775857051410}}}}
