{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775857147434,"sessionID":"ses_286ac20beffe44cAD1ncYYIIxq","part":{"id":"prt_d795451f2001nlzwlSs4j6U7Tx","messageID":"msg_d795440ca001EewuDoqx3cf4cy","sessionID":"ses_286ac20beffe44cAD1ncYYIIxq","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_e27fbbb076f74be2b59c0eef","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification: AR-014 — Valkey Store Implementation\n\n**Module:** `pkg/store`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Type:** New Feature\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis specification defines the Valkey implementation of the `Store` interface for session persistence in the AgentCube sandbox orchestration system. The Valkey store provides an alternative backend to Redis with compatible operations using the `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` client library.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### R-1: Valkey Store Structure\n\n**Given** the Valkey store implementation  \n**When** the store is instantiated  \n**Then** it SHALL have the following structure:\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Valkey store has correct fields\n  Given the valkeyStore struct is defined\n  When the struct is inspected\n  Then it SHALL have cli field of type valkey.Client\n  And it SHALL have sessionPrefix string field\n  And it SHALL have expiryIndexKey string field\n  And it SHALL have lastActivityIndexKey string field\n\nScenario: Valkey store uses same key patterns as Redis\n  Given valkeyStore constants are defined\n  When the values are checked\n  Then sessionPrefix SHALL be \"session:\"\n  And expiryIndexKey SHALL be \"session:expiry\"\n  And lastActivityIndexKey SHALL be \"session:last_activity\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-2: Valkey Client Connection Options\n\n**Given** Valkey store initialization  \n**When** connection options are built  \n**Then** the system SHALL construct `valkey.ClientOption` with:\n\n- `InitAddress`: Split from `VALKEY_ADDR` by commas\n- `Password`: From `VALKEY_PASSWORD`\n- `DisableCache`: From `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` (ParseBool, true enables)\n- `ForceSingleClient`: From `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` (ParseBool, true enables)\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Single address InitAddress\n  Given VALKEY_ADDR=\"valkey:6379\"\n  When makeValkeyOptions is called\n  Then InitAddress SHALL be []string{\"valkey:6379\"}\n\nScenario: Multiple addresses InitAddress\n  Given VALKEY_ADDR=\"node1:6379,node2:6379,node3:6379\"\n  When makeValkeyOptions is called\n  Then InitAddress SHALL be []string{\"node1:6379\", \"node2:6379\", \"node3:6379\"}\n\nScenario: Password provided\n  Given VALKEY_PASSWORD=\"secret123\"\n  When makeValkeyOptions is called\n  Then Password SHALL be \"secret123\"\n\nScenario: DisableCache enabled\n  Given VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"true\"\n  When makeValkeyOptions is called\n  Then DisableCache SHALL be true\n\nScenario: DisableCache disabled\n  Given VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"false\"\n  When makeValkeyOptions is called\n  Then DisableCache SHALL be false\n\nScenario: DisableCache invalid value\n  Given VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE=\"invalid\"\n  When makeValkeyOptions is called\n  Then DisableCache SHALL be false (ParseBool fallback)\n\nScenario: ForceSingleClient enabled\n  Given VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE=\"true\"\n  When makeValkeyOptions is called\n  Then ForceSingleClient SHALL be true\n\nScenario: ForceSingleClient disabled\n  Given VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE unset\n  When makeValkeyOptions is called\n  Then ForceSingleClient SHALL be false\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-3: Valkey Environment Variables\n\n**Given** Valkey store initialization  \n**When** environment variables are read  \n**Then** the system SHALL require/process:\n\n| Variable | Required | Notes |\n|----------|----------|-------|\n| `VALKEY_ADDR` | Yes | Comma-separated list |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD` | Yes unless `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=false` | |\n| `VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED` | No | Default `true`, case-insensitive |\n| `VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE` | No | Default `false`, ParseBool |\n| `VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE` | No | Default `false`, ParseBool |\n| `STORE_TYPE` | Must be `valkey` | Case-insensitive |\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: VALKEY_ADDR required\n  Given VALKEY_ADDR is not set\n  When Valkey store initializes\n  Then initialization SHALL fail with error indicating missing VALKEY_ADDR\n\nScenario: VALKEY_PASSWORD required by default\n  Given VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty\n  And VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED is unset\n  When Valkey store initializes\n  Then initialization SHALL fail with error stating password required\n\nScenario: VALKEY_PASSWORD disabled\n  Given VALKEY_ADDR set and VALKEY_PASSWORD empty\n  And VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED=\"false\"\n  When Valkey store initializes\n  Then connection SHALL proceed with empty password\n\nScenario: STORE_TYPE must be valkey\n  Given STORE_TYPE=\"redis\"\n  When Valkey store initialization is attempted\n  Then the Redis implementation SHALL be selected instead\n\nScenario: STORE_TYPE case insensitive\n  Given STORE_TYPE=\"VALKEY\"\n  When Storage() initializes\n  Then Valkey implementation SHALL be constructed\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-4: Ping Operation\n\n**Given** a Valkey store instance  \n**When** `Ping(ctx)` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Execute `B().Ping()` command\n- Expect string response `PONG`\n- Return error if response is not `PONG`\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Ping succeeds\n  Given a healthy Valkey server\n  When Ping(ctx) is called\n  Then B().Ping() SHALL be executed\n  And the response SHALL be \"PONG\"\n  And nil error SHALL be returned\n\nScenario: Ping fails\n  Given Valkey server is unreachable\n  When Ping(ctx) is called\n  Then B().Ping() SHALL return error\n  And non-nil error SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-5: GetSandboxBySessionID Operation\n\n**Given** a session ID  \n**When** `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Construct key as `sessionPrefix + sessionID`\n- Execute `B().Get().Key(key)`\n- Return `ErrNotFound` if `IsValkeyNil` is true\n- Decode JSON bytes to `*types.SandboxInfo` on success\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Get existing session\n  Given session \"abc-123\" exists with valid JSON data\n  When GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc-123\") is called\n  Then B().Get().Key(\"session:abc-123\") SHALL be executed\n  And JSON SHALL be decoded to *types.SandboxInfo\n  And the SandboxInfo SHALL be returned with nil error\n\nScenario: Get missing session\n  Given no key \"session:abc-123\" exists\n  When GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc-123\") is called\n  Then IsValkeyNil SHALL return true\n  And ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n\nScenario: Get with invalid JSON\n  Given key \"session:abc-123\" contains invalid JSON\n  When GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc-123\") is called\n  Then JSON decoding SHALL fail\n  And appropriate error SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-6: StoreSandbox Operation\n\n**Given** a valid `*types.SandboxInfo`  \n**When** `StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Reject nil sandbox with error\n- Reject zero `ExpiresAt` with error\n- Execute `SETNX`, `ZADD` expiry, `ZADD` last_activity in `DoMulti`\n- Use `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())` for expiry score\n- Use `float64(time.Now().Unix())` for last-activity score\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Nil sandbox rejected\n  Given StoreSandbox(ctx, nil) is called\n  When the method executes\n  Then error SHALL indicate sandbox is nil\n  And no backend operation SHALL occur\n\nScenario: Zero ExpiresAt rejected\n  Given sandbox with ExpiresAt = time.Time{}\n  When StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n  Then error SHALL indicate ExpiresAt is invalid\n  And no backend operation SHALL occur\n\nScenario: StoreSandbox succeeds\n  Given valid sandbox with SessionID=\"abc\", ExpiresAt=Unix(1000)\n  When StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n  Then DoMulti SHALL execute:\n    | Command | Key | Member | Score |\n    | SETNX | session:abc | - | - |\n    | ZADD | session:expiry | abc | 1000 |\n    | ZADD | session:last_activity | abc | <now.Unix()> |\n  And nil error SHALL be returned\n\nScenario: Duplicate store fails\n  Given session \"abc\" already exists\n  When StoreSandbox(ctx, sandbox) with same SessionID is called\n  Then SETNX SHALL return 0\n  And error SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-7: UpdateSandbox Operation\n\n**Given** an existing session  \n**When** `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox)` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Execute `SET` with `XX` option (key must exist)\n- Require response `\"OK\"` for success\n- NOT modify expiry or last-activity ZSET entries\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Update existing session\n  Given session \"abc\" exists with JSON value V1\n  When UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) with updated data is called\n  Then SET session:abc value XX SHALL be executed\n  And response SHALL be \"OK\"\n  And JSON value SHALL be updated to V2\n  And session:expiry and session:last_activity SHALL be unchanged\n\nScenario: Update missing session\n  Given session key \"session:abc\" does not exist\n  When UpdateSandbox(ctx, sandbox) is called\n  Then SET XX SHALL not update (key missing)\n  And response SHALL not be \"OK\"\n  And error SHALL be returned indicating key not exists\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-8: DeleteSandboxBySessionID Operation\n\n**Given** a session ID  \n**When** `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Execute `DEL`, `ZREM` expiry, `ZREM` last_activity in `DoMulti`\n- Remove session from all three storage locations\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Full removal\n  Given session \"abc\" exists in main key and both ZSETs\n  When DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\n  Then DoMulti SHALL execute:\n    | Command | Key | Member |\n    | DEL | session:abc | - |\n    | ZREM | session:expiry | abc |\n    | ZREM | session:last_activity | abc |\n  And all three operations SHALL succeed\n  And nil error SHALL be returned\n\nScenario: Delete non-existent session\n  Given session \"abc\" does not exist\n  When DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, \"abc\") is called\n  Then DEL and ZREM operations SHALL complete without error\n  And nil error SHALL be returned (idempotent)\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-9: ListExpiredSandboxes Operation\n\n**Given** a time `before` and limit  \n**When** `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Return `nil, nil` if `limit <= 0`\n- Execute `Zrangebyscore` with `Min(\"-inf\")`, `Max(before.Unix())`, `Limit(0, limit)`\n- Use `MGET` to load JSON for each session ID\n- Skip orphaned ZSET members (missing JSON keys)\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: List expired sessions\n  Given session:expiry contains members with scores [500, 800, 1200]\n  And before = Unix(1000) and limit = 10\n  When ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n  Then Zrangebyscore SHALL select members with scores <= 999\n  And members with scores 500 and 800 SHALL be returned\n  And MGET SHALL load JSON for each member\n  And slice of SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n\nScenario: Zero limit\n  Given limit = 0\n  When ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, before, 0) is called\n  Then nil, nil SHALL be returned immediately\n\nScenario: Orphan ZSET member skipped\n  Given session:expiry contains \"orphan\" but no session:orphan key\n  When ListExpiredSandboxes loads sessions\n  Then \"orphan\" SHALL be omitted from results\n  And no error SHALL be returned for the orphan\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-10: ListInactiveSandboxes Operation\n\n**Given** a time `before` and limit  \n**When** `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit)` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Return `nil, nil` if `limit <= 0`\n- Execute `Zrangebyscore` on `session:last_activity` with same parameters as expired\n- Use `MGET` to load JSON for each session ID\n- Skip orphaned ZSET members\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: List inactive sessions\n  Given session:last_activity contains members with scores [500, 800, 1200]\n  And before = Unix(1000) and limit = 10\n  When ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, limit) is called\n  Then Zrangebyscore SHALL select members with scores <= 999\n  And members with scores 500 and 800 SHALL be returned\n  And slice of SandboxInfo SHALL be returned\n\nScenario: Zero limit\n  Given limit = 0\n  When ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, before, 0) is called\n  Then nil, nil SHALL be returned immediately\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-11: UpdateSessionLastActivity Operation\n\n**Given** a session ID and timestamp  \n**When** `UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, sessionID, at)` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Reject empty session ID with error\n- Use `time.Now()` if `at` is zero time\n- Verify session key exists using `Exists` (must return 1)\n- Execute `ZADD` on `session:last_activity` with `float64(at.Unix())`\n- Return `ErrNotFound` if session key does not exist\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Empty session ID rejected\n  Given UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"\", time.Now()) is called\n  When the method executes\n  Then error SHALL indicate session ID is empty\n  And no backend operation SHALL occur\n\nScenario: Update last activity\n  Given session \"abc\" exists\n  And at = Unix(2000)\n  When UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at) is called\n  Then Exists(\"session:abc\") SHALL return 1\n  And ZADD session:last_activity abc 2000 SHALL be executed\n  And nil error SHALL be returned\n\nScenario: Zero time uses Now\n  Given session \"abc\" exists\n  And at = time.Time{} (zero value)\n  When UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", at) is called\n  Then ZADD SHALL use time.Now().Unix() as score\n\nScenario: Update missing session\n  Given session \"abc\" does not exist\n  When UpdateSessionLastActivity(ctx, \"abc\", time.Now()) is called\n  Then Exists SHALL return 0\n  And ErrNotFound SHALL be returned\n  And no ZADD SHALL occur\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-12: Close Operation\n\n**Given** a Valkey store instance  \n**When** `Close()` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Call `vs.cli.Close()`\n- Return `nil`\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Close connection\n  Given valkeyStore with active client connection\n  When Close() is called\n  Then vs.cli.Close() SHALL be executed\n  And nil SHALL be returned\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-13: ZSET Score Semantics\n\n**Given** ZSET operations for indices  \n**When** scores are assigned  \n**Then** the system SHALL use:\n\n- **Expiry index:** `float64(sandbox.ExpiresAt.Unix())`\n- **Last activity index:** `float64(time.Now().Unix())` on `StoreSandbox`, `float64(at.Unix())` on `UpdateSessionLastActivity`\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Expiry score from ExpiresAt\n  Given sandbox.ExpiresAt = time.Unix(1234567890, 0)\n  When StoreSandbox adds to expiry index\n  Then score SHALL be 1234567890.0\n\nScenario: Last activity score from current time\n  Given StoreSandbox is called at time.Unix(1000, 0)\n  When last-activity index is updated\n  Then score SHALL be 1000.0\n\nScenario: Last activity score from provided time\n  Given UpdateSessionLastActivity with at = time.Unix(2000, 0)\n  When last-activity index is updated\n  Then score SHALL be 2000.0\n```\n\n---\n\n### R-14: MGET Optimization Note\n\n**Given** loading multiple sessions by IDs  \n**When** `loadSandboxesBySessionIDs` is called  \n**Then** the implementation SHALL:\n\n- Build all `session:{id}` keys\n- Use single `MGET` command for batch retrieval\n- Note: Keys should be in same cluster slot for deployment consideration\n\n**Acceptance Scenarios:**\n\n```gherkin\nScenario: Batch load with MGET\n  Given session IDs [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"] all exist\n  When loadSandboxesBySessionIDs is called\n  Then single MGET session:a session:b session:c SHALL be executed\n  And all three SHALL be loaded efficiently\n\nScenario: Partial MGET results\n  Given session IDs [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"] where only \"a\" and \"c\" exist\n  When loadSandboxesBySessionIDs is called\n  Then MGET SHALL return values for \"a\", \"\", \"c\"\n  And only \"a\" and \"c\" SHALL be in returned slice\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Source | Usage |\n|------------|--------|-------|\n| `github.com/valkey-io/valkey-go` | External | Valkey client library |\n| `k8s.io/klog/v2` | External | Logging in makeValkeyOptions |\n| `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/common/types` | Internal | SandboxInfo type |\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### valkeyStore\n\n```go\ntype valkeyStore struct {\n    cli                  valkey.Client\n    sessionPrefix        string\n    expiryIndexKey       string\n    lastActivityIndexKey string\n}\n```\n\n### Environment Configuration\n\n```go\ntype ValkeyConfig struct {\n    Addr                 string   // VALKEY_ADDR (comma-separated)\n    Password             string   // VALKEY_PASSWORD\n    PasswordRequired     bool     // VALKEY_PASSWORD_REQUIRED (default true)\n    DisableCache         bool     // VALKEY_DISABLE_CACHE (default false)\n    ForceSingleClient    bool     // VALKEY_FORCE_SINGLE (default false)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Files to Create/Modify\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey.go` | Create | Valkey implementation of Store interface |\n| `pkg/store/store_valkey_test.go` | Create | Unit tests for Valkey operations |\n| `pkg/store/singleton.go` | Modify | Add valkeyStoreType constant and Valkey initialization |\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n1. **Unit Tests**:\n   - Mock Valkey client with gock/valkey mock\n   - Test all failure modes (connection errors, nil responses)\n   - Test environment variable parsing\n\n2. **Integration Tests**:\n   - TestContainer with Valkey instance\n   - Verify all Store interface operations\n   - Test ZSET score semantics\n\n3. **Compatibility Tests**:\n   - Verify same behavior as Redis implementation\n   - Test identical GIVEN/WHEN/THEN outcomes\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n- **Password Storage**: Loaded from environment variable (never committed)\n- **Connection**: TLS recommended for production Valkey connections\n- **Logging**: Password values MUST NOT be logged (use klog carefully)\n\n---\n\n## Open Questions\n\n1. Should cluster mode be explicitly supported with slot hashing?\n2. Should connection pooling parameters be configurable?\n3. Should Valkey-specific features (e.g., JSON module) be leveraged?\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/store.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/delta-spec.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/store/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775857147415,"end":1775857147429}}}}
